This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language models and their behavior on syntactically complex structures. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the behavior of neural network models. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the behavior of AI models, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it specifically focuses on neural network models, and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as it examines the ability of models to represent syntactic state over large spans of text.
